headline: Strategist talks what he's watching in healthcare, retail sectors
summary: Bogart Wealth CIO Aleks Spencer discusses his outlook on defensive trades such as the healthcare (XLV) and retail sectors (XRT). Also catch Aleks Spencer discuss the trends he is seeing in global superpowers, such as the US and China, investing in AI and rare earth mining. headline: Urban Outfitters Stock Sees RS Rating Dresses Up For Holidays
summary: One important metric to look for in a stock is an 80 or higher Relative Strength Rating.  Urban Outfitters stock now clears that threshold, with a jump from 80 to 85 Friday.  The retail stock soared after posting record Q3 earning results, amid revenue growth of 12% to $1.5 billion and a diversified strategy.

headline: Retail Stocks Move Cautiously Higher. Beware the ‘Silly Season.’
summary: Retail stocks were on track to post modest gains in Friday’s holiday-shortened trading session.  The SPDR S&P Retail ETF, also known by its ticker, XRT, was up 0.2%, compared with the S&P 500’s 0.3% gain.  Walmart stock was up 0.8%, Costco Wholesale gained 0.5%, and Target rose 1.5%.
